<component type="desktop-application">
    <id>io.github.barryran.QtScrcpy</id>

    <name>QtSrcpy</name>
    <summary>Android real-time screencast control tool</summary>

    <metadata_license>CC0-1.0</metadata_license>
    <project_license>Apache-2.0</project_license>
    <developer_name>Barry Ran</developer_name>

    <description>
        <p>QtScrcpy supports displaying and controlling Android devices via USB or over network. It
            does NOT require root privileges.</p>
        <p>It supports three major platforms: GNU/Linux, Windows and macOS.</p>
        <p>It focuses on:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>lightness</strong> (displays only the device screen)</li>
            <li><strong>performance</strong> (30~60 fps)</li>
            <li><strong>quality</strong> (1920Ã—1080 or above)</li>
            <li><strong>low latency</strong> (35~70ms)</li>
            <li><strong>low startup time</strong> (only about 1 second to display the first frame)</li>
            <li><strong>non-intrusiveness</strong> (nothing will be installed on the device)</li>
        </ul>
    </description>

